# Image Optimization

When adding or updating image assets, optimize them before they land in the project.

## Requirements

- Compress images with lossless or visually lossless settings so there is no noticeable quality loss.
- Convert raster image assets to `.webp` unless a different format is required for transparency, animation, vector artwork, or third-party constraints.
- Keep desktop image assets at or below **200 KB**.
- Keep mobile image assets at or below **100 KB**.
- Prefer separate desktop and mobile assets when responsive images need different dimensions or crops.
- Do not upscale images just to meet dimensions; export at the smallest dimensions that still look sharp in the UI.
- Use descriptive lowercase asset names and preserve existing folder conventions.

## Before Finishing

- Check the final file size of every new or changed image.
- If an image cannot meet the target budget without visible quality loss, mention the exception and why.
- Update code references when converting an existing asset to `.webp`.
